  "body": "Alternative to #15086\r\n\r\nAfter pitching my idea on [Twitter][], @gaearon mentioned that there might be a valid use case for calling `createRef()` inside function components.\r\n\r\nAs an alternative idea we could add it to the ESLint rule so that it be silenced easily.\r\n\r\nThe current implementation is very rudimentary (I somehow have the feeling that I should not pass those dependencies down to the very bottom but report earlier). Any input is greatly appreciated.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure about making it auto fixable since `useRef()` does have a different meaning than `createRef()` so we should have a human look over it I believe.\r\n\r\n[Twitter]: https://twitter.com/dan_abramov/status/1105245485487611904\r\n",
